WEBVTT

00:00:00.605 --> 00:00:02.877
Growth is not dead.

00:00:02.877 --> 00:00:04.263
(Applause)

00:00:04.263 --> 00:00:08.226
Let's start the story 120 years ago,

00:00:08.226 --> 00:00:11.858
when American factories began to electrify their operations,

00:00:11.858 --> 00:00:15.202
igniting the Second Industrial Revolution.

00:00:15.202 --> 00:00:16.313
The amazing thing is

00:00:16.313 --> 00:00:19.090
that productivity did not increase in those factories

00:00:19.090 --> 00:00:22.346
for 30 years. Thirty years.

00:00:22.346 --> 00:00:25.820
That's long enough for a generation of managers to retire.

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:28.042
You see, the first wave of managers

00:00:28.042 --> 00:00:31.459
simply replaced their steam engines with electric motors,